description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting and challenging opportunity has arisen for a suitably qualified and experienced person to join our Resuscitation Services team.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The principle role will be to support the Operational Leads in the development, organisation and facilitation of resuscitation education and training programmes for clinical staff and students form within and without the trust. You will work with a wide range of multi-professional leads throughout University Hospitals Bristol and Weston to ensure mandatory resuscitation training needs for all grades of staff are maintained in accordance with the resuscitation training needs analysis and trust policy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition, you will be expected to provide advice and support during resuscitation/ medical emergencies and undertake an agreed amount of clinical care to maintain competence, confidence, credibility and awareness of current practises in the clinical arena.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Michael Page - Resuscitation Services Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;michael.page@uhbw.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number01173420052&lt;/p&gt;
